# The Existing Loyalty Program Is Generating Cost, Not Commitment — A Complete Redesign Is Required
@type: title
@background: dark

## Loyalty Redesign
### From Points Program to Relationship Asset

@notes: The existing program has a 94% dormancy rate above the bronze tier. It is a liability masquerading as an asset. The redesign thesis is emotional engagement, not transactional points.

---

# Current program metrics reveal a structurally broken loyalty economics model
@type: stat_callout

@stat: 94% | Member Dormancy Above Bronze Tier | Members enrolled but never advancing
@stat: $47 | Cost Per Active Loyalty Member | 3× the industry benchmark of $16
@stat: 1.1× | Incremental Spend Multiplier | Near zero lift vs. non-members (benchmark: 1.6–2.0×)

@exhibit: Exhibit 1 — Loyalty Program Performance Diagnostics
@source: McKinsey Loyalty Benchmark, N=280 programs across retail, financial services, travel; 2024

@notes: The $47 cost per active member is the defining problem. Until this drops below $20, the program is a structural margin drain.

